{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GQ6GV5BdisX8PWBb8hpp9s","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 12-2: Split docker.ts, otlp.ts, beads-sync.ts, doc-health.ts\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want all 832/590/422/378-line files split into domain subdirectories,\n     9→So that the entire codebase respects the 300-line limit.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `src/lib/docker/` with `compose.ts`, `health.ts`, `cleanup.ts` and `src/lib/observability/` with `instrument.ts`, `config.ts`, `backends.ts` and `src/lib/sync/` with `beads.ts`, `sprint-yaml.ts`, `story-files.ts`, when each file is checked, then no file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given all splits complete, when `npm test` runs, then all tests pass with 0 regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→**Decision 4 (lib/ Restructuring)** and **Decision 12 (File Size Enforcement).** Four oversized files must be split.\n    19→\n    20→### docker.ts (378 lines) -> src/lib/docker/\n    21→\n    22→```\n    23→src/lib/docker/\n    24→  index.ts      — Re-exports (<50 lines)\n    25→  compose.ts    — startStack, stopStack, startSharedStack (Docker Compose operations)\n    26→  health.ts     — getStackHealth, checkDocker (health checks, port availability)\n    27→  cleanup.ts    — cleanupOrphanedContainers, cleanupVerifyEnv (container cleanup)\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→Current `src/lib/docker.ts` has compose management, health checks, and cleanup interleaved. Split by responsibility.\n    31→\n    32→### otlp.ts (422 lines) -> src/lib/observability/\n    33→\n    34→```\n    35→src/lib/observability/\n    36→  index.ts      — Re-exports (<50 lines)\n    37→  instrument.ts — instrumentProject (delegates to stack provider for package install)\n    38→  config.ts     — configureOtlpEnvVars, ensureServiceNameEnvVar (env var management)\n    39→  backends.ts   — ObservabilityBackend interface, VictoriaBackend, ElkBackend (query builders)\n    40→```\n    41→\n    42→Note: `src/modules/observability/` already exists for the observability audit module. `src/lib/observability/` is the utility layer for OTLP configuration -- different concern. The `backends.ts` file implements the `ObservabilityBackend` interface from Decision 5.\n    43→\n    44→### beads-sync.ts (590 lines) -> src/lib/sync/\n    45→\n    46→```\n    47→src/lib/sync/\n    48→  index.ts      — Re-exports (<50 lines)\n    49→  beads.ts      — bdCommand, beads CLI wrapper, BeadsNotInstalledError\n    50→  sprint-yaml.ts — generateSprintStatusYaml (from story 11-2), readSprintStatus (legacy)\n    51→  story-files.ts — readStoryFileStatus, updateStoryFile, parseStoryMarkdown\n    52→```\n    53→\n    54→### doc-health.ts (832 lines) -> src/lib/doc-health/\n    55→\n    56→```\n    57→src/lib/doc-health/\n    58→  index.ts      — Re-exports (<50 lines)\n    59→  scanner.ts    — scanDocumentation, findDocFiles\n    60→  staleness.ts  — checkStaleness, calculateDocAge\n    61→  report.ts     — generateDocHealthReport, formatFindings\n    62→```\n    63→\n    64→This is the worst violator at 832 lines. Split into scanning, staleness detection, and report generation.\n    65→\n    66→Import rule (Decision 4): All external consumers import through `index.ts` facades only.\n    67→\n    68→## Files to Change\n    69→\n    70→- `src/lib/docker.ts` — Delete after splitting into `src/lib/docker/`\n    71→- `src/lib/docker/index.ts` — Create. Re-exports\n    72→- `src/lib/docker/compose.ts` — Create. Compose operations\n    73→- `src/lib/docker/health.ts` — Create. Health checks\n    74→- `src/lib/docker/cleanup.ts` — Create. Container cleanup\n    75→- `src/lib/otlp.ts` — Delete after splitting into `src/lib/observability/`\n    76→- `src/lib/observability/index.ts` — Create