mments.\n   180→\n   181→### Import Rules (architecture-v3.md, Decision 4)\n   182→\n   183→- External consumers import from `src/lib/{domain}/index.ts` only\n   184→- Within a domain, files can import from siblings\n   185→- No cross-domain internal imports — use `../docker/index.js`, not `../docker/compose.js`\n   186→- `src/lib/state.ts` and `src/lib/output.ts` are shared utilities — any file can import them\n   187→\n   188→### Dependency Graph Within Each Domain\n   189→\n   190→**docker/**\n   191→- `health.ts` — types only, no internal deps (pure functions + execSync)\n   192→- `compose.ts` — depends on `../../templates/docker-compose.js`, may need types from `./health.js`\n   193→- `cleanup.ts` — may depend on `./health.js` for isDockerAvailable\n   194→- `index.ts` — re-exports from all three\n   195→\n   196→**observability/**\n   197→- `config.ts` — env var helpers, standalone\n   198→- `instrument.ts` — depends on `./config.js` for env var setup, `../stacks/index.js` for provider\n   199→- `backends.ts` — standalone (interface + implementations)\n   200→- `index.ts` — re-exports from all three\n   201→\n   202→**sync/**\n   203→- `story-files.ts` — depends on `../beads.js` for BeadsIssue type\n   204→- `sprint-yaml.ts` — standalone (reads/writes YAML)\n   205→- `beads.ts` — depends on `./story-files.js`, `./sprint-yaml.js`, `../beads.js`\n   206→- `index.ts` — re-exports from all three\n   207→\n   208→**doc-health/**\n   209→- `scanner.ts` — core scanning logic, types\n   210→- `staleness.ts` — depends on types from `./scanner.js`\n   211→- `report.ts` — depends on types from `./scanner.js`\n   212→- `index.ts` — re-exports from all three\n   213→\n   214→### Patterns Established by Story 12-1\n   215→\n   216→Follow the same patterns from the coverage/ split:\n   217→- Barrel index files are pure re-exports, under 50 lines\n   218→- Tests reorganized into `__tests__/` within the domain directory\n   219→- Consumer imports updated to use `/index.js` suffix\n   220→- Old monolithic file deleted (not left as stub)\n   221→- No cross-domain internal imports\n   222→- Do NOT create `AGENTS.md` in domain directories — that's a modules/ convention\n   223→\n   224→### Project Structure Notes\n   225→\n   226→- This is Story 12-2 of Epic 12 (lib/ Restructuring). Story 12-1 (coverage/ split) is the template.\n   227→- Story 12-3 will move business logic from status.ts command to a status module.\n   228→- Story 12-4 will create shared test utilities and fixtures.\n   229→\n   230→### References\n   231→\n   232→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md — Decision 4: lib/ Restructuring]\n   233→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md — Epic 12, Story 12-2]\n   234→\n   235→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   236→## Verification Requirements\n   237→\n   238→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth.proof.md`)\n   239→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   240→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   241→\n   242→## Documentation Requirements\n   243→\n   244→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   245→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth.md`\n   246→\n   247→## Testing Requirements\n   248→\n   249→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   250→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   251→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   252→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   253→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JdxXvgowBNhnosQk7Q9BkR","session_id":"849556cc-0fdf-4120-9ec0-a67b358cdbd5","uuid":"34b1f0a5-f5e3-4f91-84e3-faa3a534ea21","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:45:48.288Z"}
